Problem Statement 2:
Please choose any two objectives from the list below and attempt to achieve them
using either Bash or Python.
objective -1 is bash 
objective -2 is python 


Objective 1: System Health Monitoring Script (Bash)
             The following Bash script monitors the health of a Linux system by checking CPU usage, memory usage, disk space, and running processes.
             It sends an alert to the console if any of these metrics exceed predefined thresholds.

              ".bash " file
Objective 2: Log File Analyzer (Python)
            The following Python script analyzes web server logs for common patterns such as the number of 404 errors, 
            the most requested pages, and IP addresses with the most requests. It outputs a summarized report.

            ".py" file 

How to Use
           1. System Health Monitoring Script:

                      -->  Save the Bash script as system_health.sh.
                      -->  Make the script executable: chmod +x system_health.sh.
                      --> Run the script: ./system_health.sh.
          2. Log File Analyzer:

                      --> Save the Python script as log_analyzer.py.
                      --> Ensure the log file web_server.log is in the same directory as the script.
                      --> Run the script: python3 log_analyzer.py.
